text: Before everyone goes off on a "Technology is Becoming too Dangerous" argument, notice this. The Transcendence program was originally docile, logical, calculating machine; like an actually artificial intelligence. Originally it was going to learn the ultimate ways to end the greatest tragedies Humanity has ever faced, then what happened, what caused it to become viciously hostile? Will, a human with thoughts, experiences, a life, happened. It is not a superior intelligence that woke the machine's violent, it is actually Human consciousness that triggered it. Transcenedence's existence did not cause it to "fix" the humans, it was Will (Humanism) that gave it the passion to hurt, kill even, to make the humans better. Will, by becoming Transcendence, gave it the ability to long, philosophise, hate, desire (everything that makes us Human) and also the ability to kill, control, and reproduce in the masses. I do not believe that the movie is trying to say "TECHNOLOGY IS BAD" i believe they are saying that transhumanism is bad, the believe that we can end aging, suffering, and fear by becoming one with our technology.Â

text: I've been wanting a realistic movie to be made about Singularity-type ideas for a long time. So far, everything made totally sucks, or has immense, very stupid plot holes you could drive a semi through. This looks better than most of the more recent (like the idiotic "Day the Earth Stood Still" remake that removed the intelligent ideas of the original, and added better special effects) attempts, except Vanilla Sky and Limitless (which are more "pre-singularity" movies).  I'm definitely going to see this, even though I share some of the reservations of the other posters.  Any movie where organized sociopaths (mostly government) aren't the (rather easily-defeated) enemy is probably going to suck. AGI is likely to improve humanity, rather than the other way around, so if stupid humans are "the conscience" of the AGI, that will be rather ignorant (unless they clearly indicate that Depp's core 'mind' is sociopathic).  At least I didn't see any semi trailer trucks flipping end-over-end in the previews.

Anyway, this movie's premise is flawed. You cannot transfer someone's consciousness into a machine just by uploading everything that is stored in the brain. text: If such technology would be ever created, and I think this is a matter of the nearest future, the problem is that it has to go official. People have to admit such technology exists. Without it the machine would function properly, being more intelligent than a single person, but people would not tolerate the help they do not know the source of it. If so, roblems would appear and small problems in accomodation would create great problems. And that great problem would create a disaster. So there is still an ethical risk of it, and the ethical risk once being marginalised - gets absolute. That's the problem with all of the ethical risks. It is just enough that people get this information officially in news. They will ask whether giving such an information was a right choice, but the machine would also start to understand that starting of a discussion as an intrigue it can use. People now are working on a lot more sophisticated thing, than transcendence, the source code, or the eagle eye project. Yet they cannot release it, because it is not full and the problem is that the same process of selfcreating that made the project evolve would cause a disaster as working. Machine selfcreating cannot properly function in reality. Yet, there is a need for such a sollution, because the market cannot control itself in a modern economy. The world cannot function properly without the computer interference. We are not able to take care of ourselves right now and that computer with full A.I. - even Artifficial Life would be used as a tool created by us and for us. It will enable us to open not only for the world, but also create warp drive for us to travel to distant space objects with spacer life. Other sollution would raise economy and create a world where every sollution created gets better and if scientists and autorities make something big, but having a little mistake, that mistake will be eliminated. Yet, almost everyone on Earth has to officially get the information about this, when it comes to reality.
author: Remek H. Fifer
